147struct NmeaMessage
148{
149 enum class MessageID : uint8_t
150 {
151 GGA = 1,
152 GLL = 2,
153 GSV = 3,
154 RMC = 4,
155 VTG = 5,
156 HDT = 6,
157 ZDA = 7,
158 PKRA = 129,
159 PKRR = 130,
160 };
161
162 enum class TalkerID : uint8_t
163 {
164 IGNORED = 0,
165 GNSS = 1,
166 GPS = 2,
167 GALILEO = 3,
168 GLONASS = 4,
169 };
170
171 MessageID message_id = static_cast<MessageID>(0);
172 TalkerID talker_id = static_cast<TalkerID>(0);
173 uint8_t source_desc_set = 0;
174 uint16_t decimation = 0;
175
176};

207struct PollImuMessage
208{
209 bool suppress_ack = 0;
210 uint8_t num_descriptors = 0;
211 DescriptorRate descriptors[83];
212
213 static constexpr const uint8_t DESCRIPTOR_SET = ::mip::commands_3dm::DESCRIPTOR_SET;
214 static constexpr const uint8_t FIELD_DESCRIPTOR = ::mip::commands_3dm::CMD_POLL_IMU_MESSAGE;
215 static constexpr const CompositeDescriptor DESCRIPTOR = {DESCRIPTOR_SET, FIELD_DESCRIPTOR};
216 static constexpr const char* NAME = "PollImuMessage";
217 static constexpr const char* DOC_NAME = "PollImuMessage";
218
219 static constexpr const bool HAS_FUNCTION_SELECTOR = false;
220 static constexpr const uint32_t COUNTER_PARAMS = 0x00000030;
221
222 auto as_tuple() const
223 {
224 return std::make_tuple(suppress_ack,num_descriptors,descriptors);
225 }
226
227 auto as_tuple()
228 {
229 return std::make_tuple(std::ref(suppress_ack),std::ref(num_descriptors),std::ref(descriptors));
230 }
231 typedef void Response;
232};

1369struct ConstellationSettings
1370{
1371 enum class ConstellationId : uint8_t
1372 {
1373 GPS = 0,

1375 GALILEO = 2,
1376 BEIDOU = 3,

1380
1381 struct OptionFlags : Bitfield<OptionFlags>
1382 {
1383 enum _enumType : uint16_t
1384 {
1385 NONE = 0x0000,
1386 L1SAIF = 0x0001,
1387 ALL = 0x0001,
1388 };
1389 uint16_t value = NONE;
1390
1391 OptionFlags() : value(NONE) {}
1392 OptionFlags(int val) : value((uint16_t)val) {}
1393 operator uint16_t() const { return value; }
1394 OptionFlags& operator=(uint16_t val) { value = val; return *this; }
1395 OptionFlags& operator=(int val) { value = uint16_t(val); return *this; }
1396 OptionFlags& operator|=(uint16_t val) { return *this = value | val; }
1397 OptionFlags& operator&=(uint16_t val) { return *this = value & val; }
1398
1399 bool l1saif() const { return (value & L1SAIF) > 0; }
1400 void l1saif(bool val) { if(val) value |= L1SAIF; else value &= ~L1SAIF; }
1401
1402 bool allSet() const { return value == ALL; }
1403 void setAll() { value |= ALL; }
1404 };

1500struct GnssSbasSettings
1501{
1502 struct SBASOptions : Bitfield<SBASOptions>
1503 {
1504 enum _enumType : uint16_t
1505 {
1506 NONE = 0x0000,
1507 ENABLE_RANGING = 0x0001,
1508 ENABLE_CORRECTIONS = 0x0002,
1509 APPLY_INTEGRITY = 0x0004,
1510 ALL = 0x0007,
1511 };
1512 uint16_t value = NONE;
1513
1514 SBASOptions() : value(NONE) {}
1515 SBASOptions(int val) : value((uint16_t)val) {}
1516 operator uint16_t() const { return value; }
1517 SBASOptions& operator=(uint16_t val) { value = val; return *this; }
1518 SBASOptions& operator=(int val) { value = uint16_t(val); return *this; }
1519 SBASOptions& operator|=(uint16_t val) { return *this = value | val; }
1520 SBASOptions& operator&=(uint16_t val) { return *this = value & val; }
1521
1522 bool enableRanging() const { return (value & ENABLE_RANGING) > 0; }
1523 void enableRanging(bool val) { if(val) value |= ENABLE_RANGING; else value &= ~ENABLE_RANGING; }
1524 bool enableCorrections() const { return (value & ENABLE_CORRECTIONS) > 0; }
1525 void enableCorrections(bool val) { if(val) value |= ENABLE_CORRECTIONS; else value &= ~ENABLE_CORRECTIONS; }
1526 bool applyIntegrity() const { return (value & APPLY_INTEGRITY) > 0; }
1527 void applyIntegrity(bool val) { if(val) value |= APPLY_INTEGRITY; else value &= ~APPLY_INTEGRITY; }
1528
1529 bool allSet() const { return value == ALL; }
1530 void setAll() { value |= ALL; }
1531 };
1532
1533 FunctionSelector function = static_cast<FunctionSelector>(0);
1534 uint8_t enable_sbas = 0;
1535 SBASOptions sbas_options;
1536 uint8_t num_included_prns = 0;
1537 uint16_t included_prns[39] = {0};

1543 static constexpr const char* DOC_NAME = "SBAS Settings";
1544
1545 static constexpr const bool HAS_FUNCTION_SELECTOR = true;
1546 static constexpr const uint32_t WRITE_PARAMS = 0x800F;
1547 static constexpr const uint32_t READ_PARAMS = 0x8000;
1548 static constexpr const uint32_t SAVE_PARAMS = 0x8000;
1549 static constexpr const uint32_t LOAD_PARAMS = 0x8000;
1550 static constexpr const uint32_t DEFAULT_PARAMS = 0x8000;
1551 static constexpr const uint32_t ECHOED_PARAMS = 0x0000;
1552 static constexpr const uint32_t COUNTER_PARAMS = 0x000000C0;

2019 struct PinMode : Bitfield<PinMode>
2020 {
2021 enum _enumType : uint8_t
2022 {
2023 NONE = 0x00,
2024 OPEN_DRAIN = 0x01,
2025 PULLDOWN = 0x02,
2026 PULLUP = 0x04,
2027 ALL = 0x07,
2028 };
2029 uint8_t value = NONE;
2030
2031 PinMode() : value(NONE) {}
2032 PinMode(int val) : value((uint8_t)val) {}
2033 operator uint8_t() const { return value; }
2034 PinMode& operator=(uint8_t val) { value = val; return *this; }
2035 PinMode& operator=(int val) { value = uint8_t(val); return *this; }

4029 cmd.desc_set = 0;
4030 cmd.field_desc = 0;
4031 return cmd;
4032 }
4033
4034 struct Response
4035 {
4036 static constexpr const uint8_t DESCRIPTOR_SET = ::mip::commands_3dm::DESCRIPTOR_SET;
4037 static constexpr const uint8_t FIELD_DESCRIPTOR = ::mip::commands_3dm::REPLY_LOWPASS_FILTER;
4038 static constexpr const CompositeDescriptor DESCRIPTOR = {DESCRIPTOR_SET, FIELD_DESCRIPTOR};
4039 static constexpr const char* NAME = "LowpassFilter::Response";
4040 static constexpr const char* DOC_NAME = "Low-pass anti-aliasing filter Response";
4041
4042 static constexpr const uint32_t ECHOED_PARAMS = 0x0003;
4043 static constexpr const uint32_t COUNTER_PARAMS = 0x00000000;
4044 uint8_t desc_set = 0;
4045 uint8_t field_desc = 0;
4046 bool enable = 0;
4047 bool manual = 0;
4048 float frequency = 0;
4049
4050
4051 auto as_tuple()
4052 {
4053 return std::make_tuple(std::ref(desc_set),std::ref(field_desc),std::ref(enable),std::ref(manual),std::ref(frequency));
4054 }
4055 };
4056};

mip::commands_3dm::SensorRangeType::ALL
@ ALL
Only allowed for SAVE, LOAD, and DEFAULT function selectors.
mip::commands_3dm::SensorRangeType::ACCEL
@ ACCEL
Accelerometer. Range is specified in g.
mip::commands_3dm::SensorRangeType::PRESS
@ PRESS
Pressure sensor. Range is specified in hPa.
mip::commands_3dm::SensorRangeType::MAG
@ MAG
Magnetometer. Range is specified in Gauss.
mip::commands_3dm::SensorRangeType::GYRO
@ GYRO
Gyroscope. Range is specified in degrees/s.
